    {
      "title": "[正面] When I first downloaded this game I wan't expectin...",
      "summary": "When I first downloaded this game I wan't expecting anything amazing, but I'm glad I was wrong!\r\n\r\nThis game is great and scratches that card game itch I keep having. The game is similar to other card games on Steam (mainly Slay the Spire), but it adds progression and gacha mechanics into the mix. The game doesn't feel overly monetized or pay to win though, as I've had a very nice f2p experience, and have been able to progress at a pretty good rate. \r\n\r\nThe art and the feel of the game are also very good plus the game also just always has something to do. So I definitively recommend trying this game if you like card games, especially since it's free!",
      "source": "steam_review",
      "time": "2026-07-06T19:57:12+00:00",
